cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper discusses a multi-agent model of slime mould that exhibits complex behaviour, which suggests outsourcing of computation to the environment. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these, cs.MA and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with modelling and simulating the behaviour of a complex system without neural tissue, which is a common theme in multi-agent systems and artificial intelligence research. The other categories are also relevant, as the paper discusses the role of environmental stimuli and chemical concentration gradients in generating complex behaviour, which could be of interest to researchers working on social and information networks, neural and evolutionary computing, and systems and control.
